        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 5 at 4:30AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 429 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 8 miles
northwest of Crowell, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Margaret...                       Copper Breaks State Park...
Crowell...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
